# AWS Configuration Project
Deployed and secured a WordPress application on AWS, configured EC2 and RDS with proper authentication and access controls, implemented firewall rules, implemented Salting Hash, and hardened cloud resources.
I Built a cloud-hosted web environment, applying AWS security and foundational cloud security concepts.
Tools Used: Apache Web Server, AWS EC2, AWS RDS, MacOS, MYSQL, WordPress
Suggested order to View Files: 
1. Creating AWS EC2
2. Creating AWS RDS Database
3. Connecting EC2 Instance to RDS Database
4. EC2 Connected to RDS Instance
5. Creating Database with Wordpress
6. Authentication With Salting
7. WordPress
8. Website from WordPress
